NEWCASTLE DISEASE - DENMARK
***************************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Newcastle disease, turkeys - Denmark 980302204915
Date: Sun, 8 Mar 1998 18:36:57 -0600
From: Martin Hugh-Jones <mehj2020@vt8200.vetmed.lsu.edu>
Source: OIE Report: 6 March 1998, Vol. 11 - No. 10

Text of a fax received on 27 February 1998 from Dr E. Stougaard, Chief
Veterinary Officer, Ministry of Agriculture, Frederiksberg:
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory.
Date of initial detection of animal health incident: February 1998.
Estimated date of first infection: February 1998.
Location No. of outbreaks
Skelskoer, Vestsjaelland county 2

Description of affected population: two commercial turkey farms.
Total number of animals in the outbreaks:
susceptible 140,000

deaths Â± 2,200
Diagnosis: diagnosis made on 27 February 1998. Intracerebral pathogenicity
index: 1.75 and 1.84.
Source of agent / origin of infection: the origin of the disease is not yet
known, and is under investigation.
Control measures during reporting period: the flocks will be killed and
rendered.
